data <- read.csv("data/umr_provinsi.csv", sep = ";")
indeks_rumah <- read.csv("data/indeks_rumahcom.csv", sep = "\t") 
# indeks_rumah_bi <- read.csv("data/")
umr_jakarta <- read.csv("data/umr_jakarta.csv", sep = " ")

# clean
indeks_rumah <- indeks_rumah %>% 
  mutate(q = as.yearqtr(time, format = "Q%q %Y"),
         dt = as.Date(q),
         growth = index / lag(index) - 1)
# movement
indeks_rumah %>% 
  ggplot(aes(q, index)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point(size = 0.5) +
  labs(x = "Quarter",
       y = "Index") +
  theme_ipsum_ps(grid = "Y") +
  scale_x_yearqtr(breaks = indeks_rumah$q,
                  format = "Q%q\n'%y")


# growth
indeks_rumah %>% 
  ggplot(aes(q, growth, fill = growth > 0)) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  labs(x = "Quarter",
       y = "Growth") +
  theme_ipsum_ps(grid = "Y") +
  geom_text(data = indeks_rumah %>% 
              filter(growth > 0),
            aes(label = scales::percent(growth)),
            family = "IBMPlexSans",
            size = 2,
            vjust = 2) +
  geom_text(data = indeks_rumah %>% 
              filter(growth < 0),
            aes(label = scales::percent(growth)),
            family = "IBMPlexSans",
            size = 2,
            vjust = -1) +
  scale_fill_ipsum() +
  scale_x_yearqtr(breaks = indeks_rumah$q,
                  format = "Q%q\n'%y") +
  scale_y_percent()
indeks_rumah %>% 
  filter(dt <= ymd(20190101)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(dt)) %>% 
  mutate(r = row_number()) %>% 
  arrange(dt) %>% 
  mutate(r2 = row_number()) %>% 
  filter(r == 1 | r2 == 1) %>% 
  select(dt, index) %>% 
  mutate(growth = index / lag(index) - 1,
         growth_cagr = (index / lag(index))^(1 / (year(dt) - year(lag(dt)) + 1) ) - 1)
##           dt index growth growth_cagr
## 1 2015-01-01 100.0     NA          NA
## 2 2019-01-01 109.6  0.096      0.0185
